An integer is given. Get a description of the number as a string: "negative even number", "negative odd number", "positive odd number", "positive even number", "zero number".
Write a function called numberDescription that takes num as an argument and returns

"negative even number", if the number is negative even,
"negative odd number", if the number is negative odd,
"positive even number", if the number is positive even,
"positive odd number", if the number is positive odd,
"zero number" if the number is 0.'

function numberDescription(num){
  if (num < 0 && num % 2 === 0) 
  return 'negative even number';
  if (num < 0 && num % 2 !== 0)
  return 'negative odd number';
  if (num > 0 && num % 2 === 0) 
  return 'positive even number';
  if (num > 0 && num % 2 !== 0) 
  return 'positive odd number';
  if (num === 0) return 'zero number';
}
